SIMPLE: perficient
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Perficient
<hw>Per*fi"cient</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>perficiens</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>perficere</ets> to perform. See
<er>Perfect</er>.]</ety> <def>Making or doing thoroughly; efficient;
effectual.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Blackstone.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Perficient</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Perficient
<hw>Per*fi"cient</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who performs or perfects a
work; especially, one who endows a charity.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Perfidious</ent>⟦br⟧
